properties.sfomuseum:creditline: Gift of the Captain John B. Russell Family
properties.sfomuseum:description: a. Airmail flight cover, Pan American Airways, FAM-14, first transpacific airmail flight between San Francisco and Manila, Honolulu - Manila leg; purple stamped cachet at left with text “First flight trans-Pacific / F.A.M. Route 14 / Honolulu to Manila”; typewritten text at top left: “Via first contract trans-Pacific flight / Hawaii to Philipine [sic] Islands”; postmarked November 24, 1935 in Honolulu with four-bar cancellation over two 20-cent stamps, one 5-cent stamp, and one 6-cent postage indicia; backstamp: November 29, 1935, Manila; signed by Postmaster John W. Wilson.b. Backing sheet with two sets of mounting corners, with handwritten caption: “November 1935, Honolulu to Manila segment”, and black and white photocopy of back side of envelope with Manila receiving stamp.
